#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:5
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr "架构"

#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:7
msgid ""
"Murano uses other OpenStack services in order to prevent reimplementing of "
"existing functionality. Murano interacts with these services using their "
"REST API (via their python clients). The most used external services are "
"keystone and heat."
msgstr ""
"Murano使用了OpenStack的一些服务从而可以实现使用已经存在的功能。Murano使用它们"
"的 REST API （通过它们的python客户端）实现和这些服务的交互，最多使用的服务是"
"keystone和heat。"

#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:12
msgid ""
"Heat is used to orchestrate the infrastructural resources such as servers,"
msgstr ""
"Heat被用来编排诸如服务之类的基础设施资源。"

#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:13
msgid ""
"volumes, and networks. Murano dynamically creates the heat templates based "
"on the application definition."
msgstr ""
"卷，以及网络。Murano基于应用程序所定义的动态创建heat模板。"

#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:16
msgid ""
"All remote operations to the user’s servers are done via an AMQP queue to "
"the"
msgstr ""
"所有的对用户服务的远程操作均通过AMQP连接到murano-agent来完成。"

#: ../../draft/intro/architecture.rst:17
msgid ""
"murano-agent. Examples of this are installing and configuring software on "
"the server. Note that this communication can easily be configured on a "
"separate instance of AMQP to ensure that the infrastructure and servers are "
"isolated."
msgstr ""
"此例子即是在服务器中安装和配置软件。请注意，此处的通信可以很容易的被配置为分开的"
"AMQP的实例，从而确保基础设施和服务是隔离的。"
